-image\"/\u003e\n                \u003c/picture\u003e\n            \u003c/figure\u003e\n        \u003c/a\u003e  \n        \n\n\n\u003cp\u003eAll VW ID. Buzz trims can charge at up to 200 kWh. That’s enough to allow the van to go from 10 percent to 80 percent in 26 minutes.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCan both rear rows of seats be removed easily?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\n        \u003ca href=\"https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-73.jpg\" data-type=\"inarticle-image-block\"\u003e \n            \u003cfigure\u003e\n                \u003cpicture\u003e\n                    \u003csource type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/webp/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-73.webp 1920w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/webp/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-73-400x225.webp 400w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/webp/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-73-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/webp/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-73-768x432.webp 768w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/webp/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-73-1536x864.webp 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, (max-width: 1535px) 100vw, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, (max-width: 768px) 1000px, (max-width: 300px) 600px, (max-width: 200px) 200px\"/\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-73-1024x576.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-73.jpg 1920w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-73-400x225.jpg 400w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-73-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-73-768x432.jpg 768w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-73-1536x864.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, (max-width: 1535px) 100vw, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, (max-width: 768px) 1000px, (max-width: 300px) 600px, (max-width: 200px) 200px\" alt=\" All Your Burning VW ID.Buzz Questions Answered\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1080\" data-src=\"https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-73-1024x576.jpg\" data-type=\"inarticle-image\"/\u003e\n                \u003c/picture\u003e\n            \u003c/figure\u003e\n        \u003c/a\u003e  \n        \n\n\n\u003cp\u003eNo. The third row does pop out quite quickly. Sadly, the second row is bolted down and so owners will need to break out some tools to remove it should they basically want to convert their ID. Buzz to a cargo van.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHow is it from a noise, harshness, and vibration standpoint?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\n        \u003ca href=\"https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-28.jpg\" data-type=\"inarticle-image-block\"\u003e \n            \u003cfigure\u003e\n                \u003cpicture\u003e\n                    \u003csource type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/webp/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-28.webp 1920w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/webp/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-28-400x225.webp 400w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/webp/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-28-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/webp/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-28-768x432.webp 768w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/webp/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-28-1536x864.webp 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, (max-width: 1535px) 100vw, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, (max-width: 768px) 1000px, (max-width: 300px) 600px, (max-width: 200px) 200px\"/\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-28-1024x576.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-28.jpg 1920w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-28-400x225.jpg 400w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-28-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-28-768x432.jpg 768w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-28-1536x864.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, (max-width: 1535px) 100vw, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, (max-width: 768px) 1000px, (max-width: 300px) 600px, (max-width: 200px) 200px\" alt=\" All Your Burning VW ID.Buzz Questions Answered\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1080\" data-src=\"https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-28-1024x576.jpg\" data-type=\"inarticle-image\"/\u003e\n                \u003c/picture\u003e\n            \u003c/figure\u003e\n        \u003c/a\u003e  \n        \n\n\n\u003cp\u003eHonestly, quite good. This vehicle is well-built and doesn’t feel cheaply put together. It does seem to be a little more jarring in the cabin than expected but it also doesn’t feel like it’s going to fall apart anytime soon. The suspension is simply firmer than in most minivans.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDoes the ID. Buzz deliver on its price tag?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\n        \u003ca href=\"https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-131.jpg\" data-type=\"inarticle-image-block\"\u003e \n            \u003cfigure\u003e\n                \u003cpicture\u003e\n                    \u003csource type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/webp/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-131.webp 1920w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/webp/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-131-400x225.webp 400w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/webp/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-131-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/webp/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-131-768x432.webp 768w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/webp/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-131-1536x864.webp 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, (max-width: 1535px) 100vw, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, (max-width: 768px) 1000px, (max-width: 300px) 600px, (max-width: 200px) 200px\"/\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-131-1024x576.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-131.jpg 1920w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-131-400x225.jpg 400w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-131-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-131-768x432.jpg 768w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-131-1536x864.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, (max-width: 1535px) 100vw, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, (max-width: 768px) 1000px, (max-width: 300px) 600px, (max-width: 200px) 200px\" alt=\" All Your Burning VW ID.Buzz Questions Answered\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1080\" data-src=\"https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-131-1024x576.jpg\" data-type=\"inarticle-image\"/\u003e\n                \u003c/picture\u003e\n            \u003c/figure\u003e\n        \u003c/a\u003e  \n        \n\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf you’re someone with a bunch of free cash laying around who wants to relive the good old days, then absolutely. If you’re anyone else, probably not. Look, as I said in the full review, it’s absolutely the best vehicle on the market in terms of packaging. I hope other automakers recognize that and mimic it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMore: \u003ca href=\"https://www.carscoops.com/2024/09/brace-for-markups-as-vw-dealers-will-only-have-1-or-2-id-buzz-vans-at-launch/\"\u003eVW Dealers Will Only Get 1 Or 2 ID. Buzz Vans Each At Launch\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThat packaging though doesn’t make it worth this much cash. In fact, making it such a hardcore retro play is perhaps the biggest reason it doesn’t deliver. The original Type II bus would cost around $25,000 adjusted for inflation. This vehicle costs three times that and doesn’t come close to offering three times the value that the original did. Sure, being a much more modern vehicle, and an electric one at that, drives up costs, but if VW had managed to offer a more affordable version, it would certainly draw in a much wider audience.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\n        \u003ca href=\"https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-26-1.jpg\" data-type=\"inarticle-image-block\"\u003e \n            \u003cfigure\u003e\n                \u003cpicture\u003e\n                    \u003csource type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/webp/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-26-1.webp 1920w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/webp/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-26-1-400x225.webp 400w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/webp/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-26-1-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/webp/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-26-1-768x432.webp 768w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/webp/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-26-1-1536x864.webp 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, (max-width: 1535px) 100vw, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, (max-width: 768px) 1000px, (max-width: 300px) 600px, (max-width: 200px) 200px\"/\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-26-1-1024x576.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-26-1.jpg 1920w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-26-1-400x225.jpg 400w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-26-1-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-26-1-768x432.jpg 768w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-26-1-1536x864.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, (max-width: 1535px) 100vw, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, (max-width: 768px) 1000px, (max-width: 300px) 600px, (max-width: 200px) 200px\" alt=\" All Your Burning VW ID.Buzz Questions Answered\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1080\" data-src=\"https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Volkswagen-ID.-Buzz-for-Carscoops-by-Stephen-Rivers-26-1-1024x576.jpg\" data-type=\"inarticle-image\"/\u003e\n                \u003c/picture\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003ePhotos Stephen Rivers for Carscoops\u003c/figcaption\u003e\n            \u003c/figure\u003e\n        \u003c/a\u003e  \n        \n\n\n\n\n                        \n                    \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
